</p></li><li id="LI_BF34E76ED5674E9B956F4CD6029047EF" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Open the top cover 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-7215619B-4D8E-42B1-B219-10C1EF6B5FB5" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Do not lean on the strip support. 
</p></note></li><li id="LI_E9CEF7BDB95745EA96EC37E8D5AB5C40" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Move the printhead carriage out of the home position safely. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="05DISA36" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-8363E783-9366-44B4-B558-5F8C5D57EAA3.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 05 How to move the printhead carriage out of the home position...?>05 How to move the printhead carriage out of the home position safely</xref>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_5B7B86E524944DEDBE9D46EBE64C92BC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the maintenance tray. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="07DISA020" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-C04E8AED-532E-4792-9B1F-478E74979222.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 07 How to remove the maintenance tray?>07 How to remove the maintenance tray</xref>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_89424B06E04A4DB88A2C419E086E2958" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the knife compartment cover . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="24DISA034" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-1D8187CA-1F3B-4EBF-9E0A-F130AF910D4A.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to remove the knife compartment cover?>24 How to remove the knife compartment cover</xref> 
</p></li><li id="LI_21C8B271522344C0958B457D5D3BA087" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the right side top cover . 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">See : 
<xref keyref="24DISA042" class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-F53C0184-B1EA-4AA3-A93E-FA5DB552BE10.xml" format="dita" locktitle="yes" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?><?xm-replace_text 24 How to remove the right side top cover?>24 How to remove the right side top cover</xref> 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">See: 
<xref href="GUID-A1586343-23C1-47B2-BE4B-BB8972057671.xml" scope="local" format="dita" class="- topic/xref " type="task"><?ditaot gentext?>24 How to remove the media input right cover</xref> 
</p></li></ol></prereq><section id="GUID-E4895B67-7FC1-4974-A5C8-D34725505879" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Required tools</title><ul id="UL_88D5352595F642AFA44E04454C82A41C" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_09DFB8A70D17453A89E1C6516B69232F" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T10. 
</p></li><li id="LI_B226048C551F41A1ACE5F9B2A16D1597" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Screwdriver Torx T20. 
</p></li><li id="LI_929C0F12811B4096BB70DA320BD9C6C8" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Protective gloves: 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Microflex</b> 93-260 gloves. 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-C02D66D1-E3CC-4BC2-95F8-775D93D93431" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Warning / Caution</title><note type="caution" id="GUID-A97040BC-F110-4E4B-9CFF-E8082B9DA00E" class="- topic/note "><fig id="GUID-DB340B14-87E5-4FDB-8108-245D16C84FF1" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FCF86E23-0DD4-40BC-ACDF-FF8ABA1E6502-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">Avoid skin contact with ink: wear protective gloves. 
</p><fig id="GUID-7C716739-2AD7-42F8-8EF6-B28A8E7B1F76" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-D8099BBE-C3A2-4392-8B56-C532EDDD6073-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> Protect your eyes from splashing ink: wear safety glasses. 
</p></note></section><section id="GUID-EC9C24D5-D455-4022-B616-D7FEF4DE0A1A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Illustration</title><fig id="GUID-5415A21E-9ECE-461D-8259-FC2B6EB9AE5C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-087DADD3-1439-4A6D-93AA-A35D8A21BFE0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-087DADD3-1439-4A6D-93AA-A35D8A21BFE0-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="SECTION_10706F4338B7408BABADE578D99770E9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to remove</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_6937E5A1DB7E4095B28EBF6850698301" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Disconnect the 3 indicated connectors. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the cable bundles for the cable guides. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-08E33E97-7100-4573-B83F-2BE402163F4B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-AE0BC5C8-69C6-4A82-8902-0396DC733E31-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-AE0BC5C8-69C6-4A82-8902-0396DC733E31-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-90528DFB-392A-4FDF-8041-804EB1D8FA4A" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-4162DBAD-E03F-46F9-B728-24A6934DC617-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-4162DBAD-E03F-46F9-B728-24A6934DC617-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 2 T20 screws at the front. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-17E70B2C-6501-4040-8C8C-6A4E1C98466C" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-68167F88-4F65-44A9-A68A-1EFD4DFAC3AE-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-68167F88-4F65-44A9-A68A-1EFD4DFAC3AE-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Slide out the assembly. 
</p><note type="important" id="GUID-A6A70B35-7696-4829-AE2A-98EA5F8AFC9B" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">The cable guides tend to catch in the flat cables at the right hand side. Guide the assembly carefully. 
</p></note></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-44CB27F8-78AE-4D00-9BC3-398DF7084370" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-45C2E893-669C-4E41-954B-F398914CE455-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-45C2E893-669C-4E41-954B-F398914CE455-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-234D70A5-41EC-40E2-9E43-4217D346F540" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">How to install</title><table pgwide="1" id="TABLE_108152DDACE347E3A5658685C3B219EF" class="- topic/table "><tgroup align="left" outputclass="step" cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="40*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead valign="top" class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Step 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Action 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remarks 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody valign="top" class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Install in reverse order. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Reconnect the Service jumper, exit SDS and press 'Restart' on the operator panel. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "/></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-6C227E52-0223-48E4-A655-F691AD09A3EC.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Dis-assembly</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
